In response to national concerns, the Nigerian Navy (NN) yesterday said its 2020 recruitment exercise has been suspended indefinitely. This was contained in a statement by Director Naval Information (DINFO), Commodore Suleman Dahun. The navy commenced its online recruitment exercise on March 11 and the application process was billed to continue till April 21. Dahun said the online registration for the 2020 recruitment has been suspended and the recruitment portal deactivated till further notice.